&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position: R&amp;amp;D Engineering Intern&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Opportunity Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technergetics is searching for a full-time (30 to 40 hours per week) research intern for a 3-month engagement to support a Phase I SBIR/STTR R&amp;amp;D effort focused on secure, low-power personnel tracking for edge environments where GPS, cellular, and Wi-Fi can&#39;t be relied on. This is hands-on R&amp;amp;D (Research and Development) — protocol design, mesh networking experimentation, and documenting findings that feed directly into a follow-on proposal. Strong performers may be considered for a permanent role at the conclusion of the internship, based on company needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Details   &lt;/strong&gt;  &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay: $22-$28. &lt;/strong&gt;The hourly wage is dependent on the amount of schooling and experience of the successful candidate.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote position. &amp;nbsp;The work may be performed from the successful candidate&#39;s home. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a minimum work expectation of 30 hours per week and a maximum of 40 hours per week for this position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The start date is expected to be June 2026.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the contract requirements for this position, only U.S. citizens are eligible to apply.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities and Duties  &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The R&amp;amp;D Engineering Intern will work alongside our Principal Investigator and an academic Co-PI to research and prototype a tracking protocol inspired by military tactical data links, built on top of modern long-range/low-power IoT stacks (LoRa, Meshtastic, Thread).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Daily Activities Include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Researching mesh networking approaches for Denied, Disconnected, Intermittent, and Limited-bandwidth (D-DIL) environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comparative analysis of LoRaWAN, Meshtastic, Thread, and military tactical data link design principles (TDMA scheduling, anti-jam, time sync)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drafting a notional message format optimized for constrained RF links&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluating cluster formation strategies (entropy-based weighting, RSSI, residual energy trade-offs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lightweight crypto evaluation (PKI vs. symmetric key distribution for low-power MCUs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to the final technical report and follow-on roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with tasking under this effort that may not be specifically listed here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Certifications: &lt;/strong&gt;  &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires matriculation in an accredited college or university while pursuing a Master&#39;s Degree or a late-stage BS/BA (rising senior or final-year) in computer engineering, electrical engineering or a closely related field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coursework or project experience in at least two of: wireless communications, embedded systems, networking protocols, or applied cryptography&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with C/C++ and/or Python for embedded and simulation work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical writing — you&#39;ll co-author sections of the final report&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-directed; able to plan and execute against weekly milestones in a remote setup&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following qualifications are not required but nice to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with LoRa, LoRaWAN, Meshtastic, Thread, BLE, or Zigbee&lt;/l

